p4
VThe crystal clear rendering of M.K. Sankaran Nambudiri always hasrasikasabsorbed in the quintessence of music. The purity of &#8216;Ra ra rajeeva lochana,&#8217; a kriti of the legendary composer Mysore Vasudacharya in Mohanam, exemplified the vocalist&#8217;s prowess in Carnatic music. After an elaboration of the raga, which brought forth all its nuances, Nambudiri rendered the composition with aplomb.The kutcheri at  Sri Chembai Memorial Hall, Thiruvananthapuram, was organised by the Palghat Mani Iyer Foundation as part of the birth anniversary celebrations of the mridamgam vidwan, the late Palghat T.S. Mani Iyer.Earlier,  Nambudiri began his vocal concert with an invocation in Natta. The kriti was Thulaseevanam&#8217;s &#8216;Pranathotsmin devam vinayakan.&#8217; He followed it with Bhadrachalam Ramadas&#8217; &#8216;Paluke bangara mayana kodandapani&#8217; in Anandabhairavi, wherein the dasa implores the lord to give him a patient listening. The Ragam Tanam Pallavi in Behag stood out for its bhakti bhava. Smooth delineation of the raga was followed by tanam and a short pallavi, &#8216;Vadivelane kumarane.&#8217;Tyagaraja&#8217;s &#8216;Reminchuva evarura reghuthoma&#8217; in Suposhini, a janya of Harikambhoji, a lilting kriti, hadrasikasnodding their heads.Swati Tirunal&#8217;s &#8216;Vihara manasa&#8217; in Kapi and Tyagaraja&#8217;s &#8216;Manavinala kimchara&#8217; in Nalinakanti delighted the music buffs for these are rarely sung nowadays.Thukadas included &#8216;Reghuveerayani&#8217; (Desh), &#8216;Reghuvara&#8217; (Ahirbhairavi) and &#8216;Nache&#8217; (Basant). Nambudiri concluded his vocal recital with a tillana in Kadanakuthoohalam, composed by his guru T.V. Gopalakrishnan.Viju S.Anand&#8217;s support on the violin was commendable. The thaniavarthanam performed by  Kamalakar Rao and T.V.Vasan on the mridamgam and ghatam respectively, which lasted for more than 20  minutes, came in for much applause.
